         "id": "SECTION_introduction",
         "text": [
            {
               "text": "### Introduction\n\nIn the first text of the First Steps section, we began studying counting by arguing that our sides are equal (<htcite0>).\n\nIn the second chapter of the same section, we revisited the idea of equality by analyzing different objects and concluded that objects can be similar, but not entirely equal (<htcite1>).",
               "source": [
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "20b14681-88c0-438a-a273-a0902ae5db38",
                     "text": "History Tracers Team",
                     "page": "Our Sides Are Equal",
                     "date_time": {
                        "type": "gregory",
                        "year": "2024",
                        "month": "",
                        "day": ""
                     }
                  },
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "b5efc8f9-c268-430f-9681-7a43848ee48e",
                     "text": "History Tracers Team",
                     "page": "First Steps",
