                  }
               ],
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "markdown",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "<p><center><div class=\"first_steps_reflection_parent\"><div class=\"first_steps_reflection question_mark\"><i class=\"fa-solid fa-brain\"></i></div><div class=\"first_steps_reflection\"><b>Reflection 1: Comparing</b><br /><br />Considering what we have seen so far, we can say that:<br />Addition helps us to group things together.<br />Multiplication helps us to group equal quantities.<br />Division helps us to share.<br />Subtraction helps us to move or show change.<br/><br/>If you had to choose one of these mathematical operations to determine if something is equal, which one would you choose?</div></div></center></p>",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "html",
               "PostMention": ""
            }
         ]
      },
      {
         "id": "SECTION_body",
