            {
               "text": "### Our Body\n\nTo answer the reflection, we will use our hands as represented in **Figure 1**:",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "markdown",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "<p><table class=\"book_navigation\"><tr><td>Left hand</td><td>Right hand</td></tr><tr><td><img id=\"imgLH\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('imgLH', '0%')\" src=\"images/HistoryTracers/Left_Hand.png\" class=\"imgcenter\"/></td><td><img id=\"imgRH\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('imgRH', '0%')\" src=\"images/HistoryTracers/Right_Hand.png\" class=\"imgcenter\"/></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\"><b>Figure 1</b>: Hands reprsentation. Â© History Tracers. <span id=\"htImgCopyright\"></span></td></tr></table></p>",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "The figure shows a person's two hands raised with all fingers extended, each pointing toward a fruit.",
               "format": "html",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "#### What do I want to measure?\n\nTo test whether our hands are equal or equivalent (<htcite0>), we need to define what we will compare. For example, we can list three possible measurements:\n- Number of fingers;\n- Size of fingers;\n- Size of the hand.\n\nAfter we define what will be compared, we can estimate the desired outcome. When we say our two hands are equal, it means there are no differences between them, that the list of differences is empty; that is, equal to zero (<htcite1>).",
